{{Infobox person | name = '''Anjli Mohindra''' | image = | caption = | birth_name = Anjli Mohindra | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|02|20}} | birth_place = [[West Bridgford]], [[Nottinghamshire]], [[United Kingdom]] | occupation = [[Actress]] | years_active = 2005-present }}
'''Anjli Mohindra''' (born 20 February 1990) is an [[English people|English]] [[actress]] from [[West Bridgford]], [[Nottingham]], best known for her role in ''[[The Sarah Jane Adventures]]'' as [[Rani Chandra (The Sarah Jane Adventures)|Rani Chandra]].
==Biography== Mohindra attended [[West Bridgford Junior School]] and the [[West Bridgford School]] and plays 'Rani Chandra' in The Sarah Jane Adventures on CBBC. Mohindra is a few years older than her character in [[The Sarah Jane Adventures]].
Mohindra spent a few months at a computer software company, where she honed her dramatic skills in the call centre. She has also appeared in an episode of [[Coronation Street]] as Shareen,<ref name=" Coronation Street (2006)'">{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0763373/fullcredits#cast|title=Coronation Street (2006)|accessdate=12-12-2009}}</ref> and in an episode of [[Doctors (2000 TV series)|Doctors]].<ref name=" Doctors Goodbye Mrs Chips (2006)'">{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0766717/|title=Doctors Goodbye Mrs Chips (2006)|accessdate=12-12-2009}}</ref> She appeared as Jaz in Judith Johnson's Scary Play at the Nottingham Central Junior Television Workshop.<ref name="James Pulford went to see the Central Drama Workshop perform Scary Play by Judith Johnson'">{{cite web|url=http://www.leftlion.co.uk/articles.cfm/id/1738|title=James Pulford went to see the Central Drama Workshop perform Scary Play by Judith Johnson|accessdate=11-12-2009}}</ref>
Mohindra played a small part in an episode of teen TV series [[The Inbetweeners]],<ref name=" The Inbetweeners (2008)'">{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1236073/|title=The Inbetweeners (2008)|accessdate=12-12-2009}}</ref> and also appears briefly as Sophie Martin in episode twelve of Law and Order: UK.<ref name="Law and Order UK (2009)'">{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt1377078/|title=Law and Order UK (2009)|accessdate=12-12-2009}}</ref> Mohindra also appeared briefly as a waitress in a Pizza Hut advertisement. She also appears on Beaver Falls as Saima
